He reminds me of a child.  Very naive, but good natured.  The way he darted his eyes back and forth when he began to understand that she was calling him the father exemplified my impression of him as naive.  It was carried farther through his need to be reassured that he didnt do anything wrong.  But I thought it was good that he sat down with his son in an effort to get to know him.  I commend that.  Why did I dislike him more than I liked him?  I cant be entirely sure, but he just seemed fragile or weak.  I dont think I really understand why I felt that way.  And I feel kind of ashamed to express this.
